<subSubSection id="C346655EFFC2B23AFF46F837C7BBFFAA" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="238" pageId="7" pageNumber="237" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE336D5FFC2B23AFF46F837C7BBFFAA" blockId="7.[151,1436,1932,2030]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,1977]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="238" pageId="7" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFC2B235FF46F837C742F8F7" bold="true" box="[151,273,1932,1957]" pageId="7" pageNumber="237">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male imago of this species can be separated from all the other congeners by a combination of the following characters: (
<number id="3D9424F2FFC2B235FE45F80AC7F3F89B" box="[404,416,1969,1993]" pageId="7" pageNumber="237" value="1.0">1</number>
) costal membrane basal to bulla with 
<number id="3D9424F2FFC2B235FC98F80AC536F89B" box="[841,869,1969,1993]" pageId="7" pageNumber="237" value="10.0">10</number>
cross veins (
<figureCitation id="13672A50FFC2B235FC27F80BC269F89B" box="[1014,1082,1968,1993]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[286,1309,193,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[286,1309,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 9. Wings of male imagos. 2, Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov., forewing; 3, idem, hind wing; 4, T. sternimaculatus sp. nov., forewing; 5, idem, hind wing; 6, T. alapictus sp. nov., forewing; 7, idem, hind wing; 8, T. pinhoi sp, nov., forewing; 9, idem, hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222477/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="237">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9424F2FFC2B235FBFBF80BC269F89B" box="[1066,1082,1968,1993]" pageId="7" pageNumber="237" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
); (
<number id="3D9424F2FFC2B235FB89F80AC234F89B" box="[1112,1127,1969,1993]" pageId="7" pageNumber="237" value="2.0">2</number>
) costal and subcostal zones of the forewing translucent (
<figureCitation id="13672A50FFC2B235FE04F86EC449F8BC" box="[469,538,2005,2030]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[286,1309,193,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[286,1309,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 9. Wings of male imagos. 2, Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov., forewing; 3, idem, hind wing; 4, T. sternimaculatus sp. nov., forewing; 5, idem, hind wing; 6, T. alapictus sp. nov., forewing; 7, idem, hind wing; 8, T. pinhoi sp, nov., forewing; 9, idem, hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222477/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="237">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9424F2FFC2B235FDDBF86EC449F8BC" box="[522,538,2005,2030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="237" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
); (
<number id="3D9424F2FFC2B235FDE8F86EC414F8BF" box="[569,583,2005,2029]" pageId="7" pageNumber="237" value="3.0">3</number>
) forewing hyaline with cross veins tinged with brown, with a central brown spot on MA fork (
<figureCitation id="13672A50FFCDB23AFEBBFF2CC7E3FFE2" box="[362,432,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[286,1309,193,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[286,1309,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 9. Wings of male imagos. 2, Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov., forewing; 3, idem, hind wing; 4, T. sternimaculatus sp. nov., forewing; 5, idem, hind wing; 6, T. alapictus sp. nov., forewing; 7, idem, hind wing; 8, T. pinhoi sp, nov., forewing; 9, idem, hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222477/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13672A50FFCDB23AFE6FFF23C78DFFE2" box="[446,478,152,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1784,1807]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1763]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 30. Thraulodes alapictus sp. nov.: 27, lateral view; 28, dorsal view; 29, detail of prosternum; 30, lateral view of female imago (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222481/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">27</figureCitation>
); (
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFE2CFF23C45FFFE2" box="[509,524,152,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="4.0">4</number>
) two dark brown bands in median region of femora (
<figureCitation id="13672A50FFCDB23AFBA2FF2CC2A6FFE2" box="[1139,1269,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1784,1807]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1763]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 30. Thraulodes alapictus sp. nov.: 27, lateral view; 28, dorsal view; 29, detail of prosternum; 30, lateral view of female imago (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222481/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Fig. 27, 30</figureCitation>
); (
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFAC4FF2CC370FFE2" box="[1301,1315,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="5.0">5</number>
) spines of penes long and narrow, apicolateral area forming an “ear”, lateral pouch absent, and without recurved folds parallel to inner margin (
<figureCitation id="13672A50FFCDB23AFE83FF64C788FFAA" box="[338,475,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[195,1406,193,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[170,1412,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 17. Genitalia of male imagos. 10, Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov., genitalia (ventral view); 11, idem, penes (ventral view); 12, T. sternimaculatus sp. nov., genitalia (ventral view); 13, idem, penes (ventral view); 14, T. alapictus sp. nov., genitalia (ventral view); 15, idem, penes (ventral view); 16, T. pinhoi sp, nov. genitalia (ventral view); 17, idem, penes (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222478/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFE43FF64C788FFAA" box="[402,475,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C346655EFFCDB23AFF16FEBFC7C8FA07" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE336D5FFCDB23AFF16FEBFC3C5FE4F" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1977]" box="[199,1430,260,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFCDB23AFF16FEBFC709FE4F" bold="true" box="[199,346,260,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Male imago.</emphasis>
Length: body, 
<quantity id="4CA49B30FFCDB23AFDD0FEBFC435FE4E" box="[513,614,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="11.5">11.5 mm</quantity>
; forewing, 
<quantity id="4CA49B30FFCDB23AFD32FEBFC51BFE4E" box="[739,840,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1099999999999999" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="11.1">11.1 mm</quantity>
; hind wings, 
<quantity id="4CA49B30FFCDB23AFC0AFEBFC260FE4E" box="[987,1075,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
; general coloration light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336D5FFCDB23AFF16FE9CC48EFE37" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFCDB23AFF16FE9CC757FE12" box="[199,260,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13672A50FFCDB23AFEC5FE9CC7CCFE12" box="[276,415,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1784,1807]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1763]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 30. Thraulodes alapictus sp. nov.: 27, lateral view; 28, dorsal view; 29, detail of prosternum; 30, lateral view of female imago (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222481/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFE85FE93C7CCFE12" box="[340,415,296,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="27.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="27.0">27–28</number>
</figureCitation>
): black; antenna light brown with scape brown; upper portion of eye reddish brown, lower portion black; ocelli white with a black ring at base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336D5FFCDB23AFF16FED4C408FEA7" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFCDB23AFF16FED4C74BFEDA" box="[199,280,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13672A50FFCDB23AFEF9FED4C7E7FEDA" box="[296,436,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1784,1807]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1763]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 30. Thraulodes alapictus sp. nov.: 27, lateral view; 28, dorsal view; 29, detail of prosternum; 30, lateral view of female imago (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222481/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFEB8FECBC7E7FEDA" box="[361,436,368,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="28.5" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="28.0">28–29</number>
</figureCitation>
): pro-, meso and metanotum brown. Pronotum with a medial triangular dark spot. Meso and metanotum light brown with sutures dark brown; recurrent scuto-scutellar suture brown. Pleura whitish washed with some red spots; episternum of prothorax white tinged with purple; mesosternum dark brown with a medial white macula; metasternum dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336D5FFCDB23AFF16FDBAC754FDFA" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFCDB23AFF16FDBAC759FD4A" box="[199,266,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13672A50FFCDB23AFECAFE44C7DAFD4A" box="[283,393,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[286,1309,193,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[286,1309,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 9. Wings of male imagos. 2, Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov., forewing; 3, idem, hind wing; 4, T. sternimaculatus sp. nov., forewing; 5, idem, hind wing; 6, T. alapictus sp. nov., forewing; 7, idem, hind wing; 8, T. pinhoi sp, nov., forewing; 9, idem, hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222477/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFE8AFE44C7DAFD4A" box="[347,393,511,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
</figureCitation>
): membrane of forewing hyaline, tinged with light brown on fork of MA vein, and with dark spot near base; costal and subcostal zones translucent. Longitudinal veins light brown; costal and subcostal cross veins blackish, lighter towards apex. Veins ICu 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFD69FDF3C496FD32" box="[696,709,584,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="2.0">2</number>
and CuP joined basally. Costal membrane with 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFB29FDF3C347FD32" box="[1272,1300,584,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="10.0">10</number>
cross veins basal to bulla and 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFEB5FDD7C7D3FDD7" box="[356,384,620,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="15.0">15</number>
cross veins distal to bulla. 
<collectingCountry id="F34B7645FFCDB23AFD63FDD7C4B9FDD7" box="[690,746,620,645]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing hyaline with 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFC15FDD7C5B3FDD6" box="[964,992,620,644]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="13.0">13</number>
light brown cross veins, with dark spot near base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336D5FFCDB23AFF16FD0EC4E0FC47" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFCDB23AFF16FD0EC6AFFD9E" box="[199,252,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Legs</emphasis>
: legs with femur yellowish, apical 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFD4CFD0FC4F4FD9E" box="[669,679,692,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFD63FD0FC493FD9E" box="[690,704,692,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="3.0">3</number>
of femur tinged with reddish followed by two black marks in median region, apex black; tibiae yellowish with apex black and a small blackish spot on the base; tarsi yellowish tinged with black with the last tarsomere darker.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336D5FFCDB23AFF16FCA4C59EFCF6" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFCDB23AFF16FCA4C762FC6A" box="[199,305,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13672A50FFCDB23AFE91FCA4C798FC6A" box="[320,459,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1784,1807]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1763]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 30. Thraulodes alapictus sp. nov.: 27, lateral view; 28, dorsal view; 29, detail of prosternum; 30, lateral view of female imago (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222481/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFEAEFC9BC798FC6A" box="[383,459,800,824]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="27.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="27.0">27–28</number>
</figureCitation>
): general coloration translucent brown; tergum I brown washed with black; terga II–VI translucent brown with anterolateral dark spots and a medial light brown macula decreasing toward tergum VI; terga IV–VI with minute medial dark spots; terga VII brown; VIII–X reddish brown. Sternum I–II brown; sterna III–VI translucent, VII–IX whitish; four minute marks on sterna III–VIII.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336D5FFCDB23AFF16FC14C4CBFB0A" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFCDB23AFF16FC14C762FC9A" box="[199,305,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13672A50FFCDB23AFE90FC14C796FC9A" box="[321,453,943,968]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[195,1406,193,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[170,1412,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 17. Genitalia of male imagos. 10, Thraulodes luizgonzagai sp. nov., genitalia (ventral view); 11, idem, penes (ventral view); 12, T. sternimaculatus sp. nov., genitalia (ventral view); 13, idem, penes (ventral view); 14, T. alapictus sp. nov., genitalia (ventral view); 15, idem, penes (ventral view); 16, T. pinhoi sp, nov. genitalia (ventral view); 17, idem, penes (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222478/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
Figs 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFEAAFC14C796FC9A" box="[379,453,943,968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
</figureCitation>
): forceps whitish with inner margin washed with black. Posterior margin of subgenital plate rounded with a minute medial projection. Penes yellowish washed with black on ventral inner region; 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFA88FC6FC334FCBE" box="[1369,1383,980,1004]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFAA1FC6FC32FFCBE" box="[1392,1404,980,1004]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="3.0">3</number>
of penes divided apically, with a pair of long and narrow spines, 3.0x the width of penes; apicolateral area forming an “ear”; external margin not forming lateral pouch and without recurved folds parallel to inner margin. Terminal filament whitish with base of segments black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336D5FFCDB23AFF16FBDFC748FA62" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFCDB23AFF16FBDFC723FB2F" bold="true" box="[199,368,1124,1149]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Female imago</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13672A50FFCDB23AFEAEFBDFC786FB2E" box="[383,469,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1784,1807]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1763]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 30. Thraulodes alapictus sp. nov.: 27, lateral view; 28, dorsal view; 29, detail of prosternum; 30, lateral view of female imago (scales: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222481/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9424F2FFCDB23AFE64FBDFC786FB2E" box="[437,469,1124,1148]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
). Length: body, 
<quantity id="4CA49B30FFCDB23AFD5CFBDFC4A7FB2E" box="[653,756,1124,1148]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.19" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="11.9">11.9 mm</quantity>
; forewing, 
<quantity id="4CA49B30FFCDB23AFCA4FBDFC58EFB2E" box="[885,989,1124,1148]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1099999999999999" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="11.1">11.1 mm</quantity>
; hind wing, 
<quantity id="4CA49B30FFCDB23AFBB8FBDFC290FB2E" box="[1129,1219,1124,1148]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
; general coloration brown. 
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFCDB23AFF21FB3CC77EFBF2" box="[240,301,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Head</emphasis>
: black ventrally and whitish tinged with purple dorsally. 
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFCDB23AFC1CFB3CC24CFBF2" box="[973,1055,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum brown with a medial dark line. Mesonotum and metanotum light brown with sutures whitish. Prosternum purple with median region whitish. Mesosternum purple with episternum and furcasternum brown. Metasternum brown. 
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFCDB23AFB66FB6AC2BFFBBA" box="[1207,1260,1233,1256]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Legs</emphasis>
: Same as male, except by general coloration of femora and tibiae darker. Abdomen entirely dark brown without segments translucent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336D5FFCDB23AFF16FA87C7C8FA07" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1977]" box="[199,411,1340,1365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B928EAC7FFCDB23AFF16FA87C775FA07" bold="true" box="[199,294,1340,1365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="238">Nymph.</emphasis>
Unknown
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
